50%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margi=
n-bottom:0px;">Meanwhile, it=E2=80=99s been fascinating to watch how <stron=
g>Shawn Carter
</strong>(a.k.a. Jay-Z) has handled the recent sexual misconduct allegation=
 against him=E2=80=A6 and let=E2=80=99s just say it=E2=80=99s been nothing =
like Baldoni=E2=80=99s approach. For starters, the hip-hop mogul has always=
 been <em>intensely</em> private. It was only a few years ago, in the midst=
 of a 12-year odyssey to trademark the name of their daughter <strong>Blue =
Ivy</strong>, that he and <strong>Beyonc=C3=A9</strong> insisted on an unpr=
ecedented protective order aimed at keeping the time and location of deposi=
tions away
from paparazzi. (Incidentally, they finally got the trademark approved on N=
ew Year=E2=80=99s Eve.)<br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px=
;">So you can imagine what unfolded when the <strong>Sean Combs</strong> (a=
=2Ek.a. Diddy) scandal erupted, and <st=
rong>Tony Buzbee</strong>, the attorne=
y representing the alleged victims, started name-dropping the rapper=E2=80=
=99s famous friends as potential collateral damage. Buzbee sent Jay-Z a dem=
and letter seeking a payout for two of his clients=E2=80=94or else, he impl=
ied,
a =E2=80=9Cpublic spectacle=E2=80=9D would ensue.<br/><br/></p><p style=3D"=
margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">The subsequent events appear destined for law =
school textbooks. Represented by Quinn Emanuel=E2=80=99s <strong>Alex Spiro=
</strong>, Jay-Z <em>didn=E2=80=99t</em> negotiate. Instead, he preemptivel=
y filed a =E2=80=9CJohn Doe=E2=80=9D extortion complaint against Buzbee. Th=
at prompted Buzbee to double down, not only moving ahead with a lawsuit acc=
using Jay-Z of sexual assault, but also hitting back at Quinn Emanuel with =
an explosive barratry
claim. (A good term to drop at dinner parties, <em>barratry</em> refers to =
filing a frivolous lawsuit just to harass someone.) According to Buzbee, pe=
ople working for Carter and Quinn Emanuel started sniffing around Texas, fl=
ashing badges, and posing as state officials to pressure his current and fo=
rmer clients into filing ethics complaints against Buzbee=E2=80=99s firm.<b=
r/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">This past week, the se=
xual assault suit against Jay-Z was dropped, but the legal
brawl over aggressive lawyering rages on. In response to Jay-Z=E2=80=99s ex=
tortion claim, Buzbee has filed an anti-SLAPP motion, arguing that the rapp=
er is infringing on constitutionally protected speech. And in a twist of fa=
te, Buzbee is being represented by <strong>Camille Vasquez</strong>=E2=80=
=94the attorney who made her name torching <strong>Amber Heard</strong> dur=
ing the <strong>Johnny Depp</strong> defamation trial. This time, she=E2=80=
=99s in court defending the First Amendment right to lob a sexual assault
claim, demand a settlement, and threaten reputational damage if it=E2=80=99=
s not paid.=C2=A0<br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Tod=
ay, a hearing was convened to discuss the matter, with Los Angeles Superior=
 Court Judge <strong>Mark Epstein</strong> telling the parties he had a har=
d time viewing Buzbee=E2=80=99s demand letters as attempted extortion. Acco=
rding to a rather lengthy tentative ruling, which Epstein held off on adopt=
ing for now, the judge found a corollary with a case that ensnared
attorney <strong>Marty Singer</strong> a few years ago. That case, also con=
cerning a demand letter (Singer sent a draft copy of a complaint and threat=
ened to fill in the blanks with tales of how his adversary used company res=
ources to have sexual affairs), went up to a California appeals court, with=
 the <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt=
2UktxclJLZ0dWUUJjRms5a0hrV2FfV3ZUaXdZbz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuaG9sbH=
l3b29kcmVwb3J0ZXIuY29tL2J1c2luZXNzL2J1c2luZXNzLW5ld3MvaG9sbHl3b29kLWxhd3llc=
nMtbWVuYWNpbmctbGV0dGVyLXByb3RlY3RlZC01ODYyMTgvP3V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1XaGF0K0kl=
MjdtK0hlYXJpbmclMkIrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgyJTJGMjUlMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9=
jb250ZW50PVdoYXQrSSUyN20rSGVhcmluZyUyQistK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODIlMkYyNSUyRj=
I1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25cdTAwMjZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWN1c3Rvb=
WVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwiaW50ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2=
MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjoyMDk1MTgwfQ/be396604f30b6ebce27ecd9c93a5=
df735258e3bf0b05e5ace46038c4c3092809" style=3D"text-decoration:underline;co=
lor:#d40000;">ultimate decision</a> being
that Singer=E2=80=99s threats didn=E2=80=99t rise to criminal behavior. (He=
 hadn=E2=80=99t expressly threatened to disclose wrongdoing to a prosecutin=
g agency or the public=E2=80=94at least directly.) Similarly, Epstein noted=
 that Buzbee=E2=80=99s behavior fell =E2=80=9Cwell short of threatening to =
go to the police <em>unless</em> Carter pays up,=E2=80=9D adding that =E2=
=80=9Cselling silence for money in the civil context is not extortion; it i=
s a settlement with a nondisclosure element.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/></p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">However, Epstein
seemed more open to Jay-Z continuing to pursue Buzbee for defamation, so lo=
ng as the hip-hop mogul could demonstrate that a reasonable person would th=
ink of <em>him </em>when Buzbee told <strong>Piers Morgan</strong> he had a=
 =E2=80=9Clong list of names=E2=80=9D who had committed assault alongside D=
iddy. At the hearing, Epstein quizzed Quinn Emanuel partner <strong>Robert =
Schwartz</strong> about whether Jay-Z could also satisfy the need to demons=
trate actual malice.=C2=A0<br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;">While
all of Buzbee=E2=80=99s statements may not make the cut, three of them seem=
 like they very well might=E2=80=94including what Buzbee <a href=3D"https:/=
/email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dWUUJjRms5a0=
hrV2FfV3ZUaXdZbz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudG16LmNvbS8yMDI0LzEyLzEwL3Rvb=
nktYnV6YmVlLXJlc3BvbmRzLWpheXotc2V4dWFsLWFzc2F1bHQtY3JpbWluYWwtY29tcGxhaW50=
Lz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249V2hhdCtJJTI3bStIZWFyaW5nJTJCKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MiU=
yRjI1JTJGMjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fY29udGVudD1XaGF0K0klMjdtK0hlYXJpbmclMkIrLStTVU=
JTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgyJTJGMjUlMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWxfYWN0aW9uX=
HUwMDI2dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1jdXN0b21lci5pb1x1MDAyNnV0bV90ZXJtPWY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFi=
ZDEyYSIsImludGVybmFsIjoiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6MjA5NTE4MX0=
/9d9bd2b1599dddf874ae27c3143191c28db7fb41c70225a22260b07fb6c83ff9" style=3D=
"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">told TMZ</a> in December: =E2=80=
=9CBuzbee said he=E2=80=99s not ruling out filing rape charges against Jay =
with New York authorities.=E2=80=9D A decision should be coming shortly, an=
d if Buzbee can=E2=80=99t escape the case, he can appeal. Between this case=
 and
Baldoni=E2=80=99s, attorneys handling high-profile sexual assault allegatio=
ns will have plenty to consider.</p></div>
