n-bottom:0px;">Every so often, a court ruling catches me off guard. <strong=
>Francis Ford
Coppola</strong>=E2=80=99s defamation lawsuit against <em>Variety, </em>whi=
ch I had pegged as a vanity project=E2=80=94just like <em>Megalopolis</em>=
=E2=80=94is moving forward, thanks to a judge=E2=80=99s ruling that the leg=
endary filmmaker has a probability of prevailing.<br/>=C2=A0</p><p style=3D=
"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">If you recall, <em>Variety</em> had followed =
up on reports from other outlets alleging that Coppola tried to kiss some s=
cantily clad female extras during the filming of last year=E2=80=99s
<em>Megalopolis</em>. The <strong>Jay Penske</strong>-owned publication obt=
ained video of the alleged incident, and interviewed crewmembers who accuse=
d the 85-year-old of being unprofessional on set. In his $15 million claim,=
 Coppola asserted that <em>Variety</em> improperly relied on anonymous sour=
ces. <em>Variety</em> responded with an anti-SLAPP motion, questioning how =
Coppola could possibly win a case, given that he conceded he kissed and hug=
ged actresses, appeared in multiple shots himself,
and didn=E2=80=99t dispute the authenticity of the published videos or the =
lack of intimacy coordinators on set. What,<em> Variety</em>=E2=80=99s atto=
rneys wanted to know, was defamatory? What would be the basis for damages?<=
br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Los Angeles Superior =
Court Judge <strong>Christopher Lui</strong> has provided an answer. In a 1=
9-page decision (<a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImR=
nVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dWUUJjRms5a0hrV2FfV3ZUaXdZbz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly=
93d3cuZG9jdW1lbnRjbG91ZC5vcmcvZG9jdW1lbnRzLzI1NTQ0MDk3LWNvcHBvbGEtc2xhcHAtc=
nVsaW5nLz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249V2hhdCtJJTI3bStIZWFyaW5nJTJCKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMr=
JTI4MiUyRjI1JTJGMjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fY29udGVudD1XaGF0K0klMjdtK0hlYXJpbmclMkI=
rLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgyJTJGMjUlMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWxfYW=
N0aW9uXHUwMDI2dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1jdXN0b21lci5pb1x1MDAyNnV0bV90ZXJtPWY2YzYwNjE3Z=
GE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImludGVybmFsIjoiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6MjA5=
NTE4Mn0/97cc24f1a30e831e80ffa564dab14e6a2d7334d70483f8e154ca0e141fd374f6" s=
tyle=3D"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">read
it in full here</a>), Lui calls out <em>Variety</em> for reporting that Cop=
pola <em>inadvertently</em> inserted himself into shots, which could imply =
he was an incompetent director. Coppola, in a declaration in the case, had =
said he was deliberately evoking a Studio 54 nightclub vibe, where celebrit=
ies would naturally appear. <em>Variety</em>=E2=80=99s sources from the mov=
ie set, Coppola claimed, knew this. Because the article impugned Coppola=E2=
=80=99s professionalism, the judge says this could rise to
defamation <em>per se</em>=E2=80=94meaning Coppola wouldn=E2=80=99t need to=
 prove special damages.<br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px=
;">As for the video=E2=80=A6 did it show kissing, or just Coppola leaning i=
n and whispering? Were the extras genuinely uncomfortable? <em>Variety</em>=
 spoke to crewmembers who interpreted the events one way, but Judge Lui not=
ed that framing a statement as an opinion doesn=E2=80=99t necessarily shiel=
d it from being considered a provably false fact. As for the claim that the=
 videos
=E2=80=9Cappear to corroborate=E2=80=9D unwanted kissing? Lui says <em>let =
a jury decide</em>. Of course, <em>Variety</em> would prefer to let its <em=
>readers</em> decide.=C2=A0<br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;">So, this on=
e is likely headed to trial=E2=80=94though an appeal has already been filed=
, since anti-SLAPP rulings in California can be immediately challenged. If =
it doesn=E2=80=99t settle, look for a possible courtroom showdown between o=
ne of the world=E2=80=99s most famous directors and one of Hollywood=E2=80=
=99s largest trade
publications. Naturally, all the Penske outlets are covering this ruling as=
 aggressively as they are the Lively-Baldoni fight. Just kidding.</p></div>
